latestIgtvVideos.title: MUTTON KORMA || DAWAT-E-SPECIAL
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
If you always wanted to relish the wedding style korma at home than this is the right recipe for you. 
Infact, if you have special house-party and your guest also love nonveg then you can prepare this and serve it as main dish.
There can be so many ways a korma can be made this is one of my personal favourite version where the mutton is cooked on low flame with myriad of spices and herbs until it turns succulent and juicy. 
The speciality of Dawat-e-Special mutton korma is it's thick and spicy gravy that has the sweetness of onion and creamy texture of curd along with aromas of spices and royalty of nuts.
Method✨
first step is Marinating mutton 
for that in a bowl add 1 kg mutton,sprinkle kewda water 1tsp, giner garlic paste-2tbsp curd-4tbsp elachi power-1/2tsp cloves-8-9 elachi-8-9 bayleaf -2 star anise-1-2 cinnamon stick-1-2  mix well and keep it aside for 20-30min.
Now the next step is to make masala for that blend 2medium sized onion in the same paste add coriander powder (2tbsp) red chilly powder (1tbsp)a pinch of turmeric powder, degi mirch (1tsp) coconut powder (2tbsp), garam masala(1/2tsp) water and mix them well.
Now, in a deep vessel add refine oil(200grms)once the oil gets hot add 2 big size thin sliced crushed onions fry them till colour changes to light brown then add foxnuts fry both of them till crispy and brown then take them out onto a palte and keep it aside.In the same oil add ghee -2tbsp add marinated chicken and spices paste mix well then add some crushed fried onion cover with lid and cook for about 3-4 min on high flame. remove lid and cook again till oil separates then add water and cook for 30 minute on medium-low flame. 
once the mutton is tender add blended fried makhana (foxnuts ) and onion. 
at last add essence power by crushing (mace,nutmeg and cardamom). 
Enjoy the lavish mutton korma.

latestIgtvVideos.title: street style chicken rolls recipe||easiest way
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Crispy and flaky Laccha paratha stuffed with flavourful chiken filling with the hint of smoke makes these rolls taste irresistibly delicious.
this is one of my personal favourite recipe that is simple yet so good😋  let's see how I made it ?
in a bowl add chicken 1/2 kg bone less.
curd 1/2 cup
ginger garlic paste -1tbsp
red chilly powder -1tsp or (to taste)
lemon juice -1small
roasted cumin powder-1/2tsp
black pepper powder-1/2tsp
salt to taste
garam masala -1/4tsp
food colour and mix everything together and keep it in refrigerator for at least 2 hours 
then take out the marinated chicken and fry it in oil once it get fried give it the smoke using coal that will give a smokey flavour to chicken. 
now the second step is making of parathas.
for making paratha first knead the dough for that in a bowl add 
maida 1/2kg  and wheat flour-1cup(optional) 
salt, refine oil, milk(optional), and water 
knead soft dough let it rest for 20-30 min then take out dough and make parathas using plated technique shown in the video.
third step is to make dips and chutney
I have used a simple mix of mayonnaise and tomato ketchup to make a dip and for making chutney in a mixer add
garlic -5 piece
green chillies-4-5
coriander
salt to taste
lemon juice 
water
curd-1/2 cup
blend it
now, peal and cut the onion into thick slices and separate the rings.
for assembly
take a paratha spread the Mayonnaise dip add chiken slices and sliced onion add lemon(if required) add green chutney or white mayonnaise (optional).
you can add more dips of your choice. 
enjoy the most delicious street style chicken rolls at your home.
